																		Never. Again.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252360" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;" >Ihp</a></span> <span class="odate time_1572309039 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Oct 2019 00:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4409078">
									

<p>I now know the pain a programmer feels when they miss a closed parentheses. You think Listpages is hard? If you do more than about 20 of these, there's a 70% chance the entire code will fall apart. There are thirty-eight &quot;Tweets&quot; on here.</p>
<p>Staff will just have to trust all the images are compliant, there are a <em>lot</em> of them and I don't have access to all of the links I used on my laptop. When I get home from vacation, I'll post the proof of compliance.</p>
<p>Onto some stuff that's not me ranting about the technical side of things:</p>
<ul>
<li>Three Portlands is an&#8230; interesting setting. It seems like one of those things that would work better in a canon where the Foundation flat-out didn't exist, honestly. I've been curious about it, but the hub (while not as bad as the Fifthism hub) leaves a bit to be desired. Plus, the whole Anderson Robotics arc kind of happened during my hiatus from the site, so I don't know what the hell their deal is, and I'm not sure where to start looking.</li>
<li>Then you have Deer College, which is based in 3ports. I think. I was attracted to this for Black Autumn 3 after seeing that they literally have a group of Eris-worshipers on campus. &quot;Hey, they worship apples of discord, I <em>have</em> apples of discord, let's do this shit!&quot;</li>
<li>This is the one I'm most hesitant about posting because, again: it seems like 3ports and Deer seem to want to exist outside of Foundation canon, and it's a bit hard to try to tie Sloth's Pit and the apples into it. I think I made it work, though.</li>
<li>The &quot;Gotham Ghosts&quot; call-out is a reference to the TV Show &quot;Evil&quot;, one of the stupidest attempts at horror I have <em>ever</em> seen on network TV. It was originally going to be a jab at Ghost Adventures, before I realized that they're a garbage group of hucksters. &quot;GhostHuntUK&quot; is a reference to <em>The Magnus Archives</em>, because if there can't be a crossover due to licensing issues, I will still have my <em>implications</em>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Thank you SO MUCH to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dyslexion" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5549954); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5549954&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1572310999" alt="Dyslexion" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5549954)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dyslexion" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5549954); return false;">Dyslexion</a></span> for writing the note used in one of the last tweets, and for encouraging me to not to just stick to one teratophilia joke.</p>

							</div>

								
